# Essential to know
- Element: `p {}`, Class: `.btn {}`, ID: `#header {}`
- Combinators: `div p` (descendant), `div > p` (child)
- Pseudo-classes: `:hover`, `:focus`, `:first-child`
- Specificity: ID > Class > Element

---

# CSS Selectors

Selectors are how you target HTML elements to apply styles. Understanding them is fundamental to writing maintainable CSS.

## Basic Selectors

### Element Selector
Targets all instances of an HTML element:

```css
/* All paragraphs */
p {
  color: #333;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* All buttons */
button {
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

### Class Selector
Targets elements with a specific class attribute (most common):

```css
/* Elements with class="btn" */
.btn {
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Multiple classes on same element */
.btn.primary {
  background: blue;
  color: white;
}
```

**HTML:**
```html
<button class="btn">Default</button>
<button class="btn primary">Primary</button>
```

### ID Selector
Targets a single element with a specific ID (use sparingly):

```css
/* Element with id="header" */
#header {
  background: #1a1a1a;
  padding: 1rem;
}
```

**HTML:**
```html
<header id="header">...</header>
```

## Combinators

### Descendant Selector (Space)
Selects elements that are descendants (any level deep):

```css
/* All .card elements inside article */
article .card {
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

/* All paragraphs inside section */
section p {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
}
```

### Child Selector (>)
Selects only direct children:

```css
/* Only direct children */
.card > .title {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
```

**HTML:**
```html
<div class="card">
  <h2 class="title">Direct child - styled ✓</h2>
  <div class="content">
    <h2 class="title">Not direct child - not styled ✗</h2>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Adjacent Sibling (+)
Selects the element immediately following another:

```css
/* First paragraph after h2 */
h2 + p {
  margin-top: 0;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

### General Sibling (~)
Selects all siblings following an element:

```css
/* All paragraphs following h2 */
h2 ~ p {
  color: #666;
}
```

## Pseudo-classes

### State Pseudo-classes
```css
/* Hover state */
.btn:hover {
  background: #0056b3;
}

/* Focus state (accessibility!) */
input:focus {
  outline: 2px solid blue;
  border-color: blue;
}

/* Disabled state */
button:disabled {
  opacity: 0.5;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

/* Checked state */
input[type="checkbox"]:checked + label {
  text-decoration: line-through;
}
```

### Structural Pseudo-classes
```css
/* First child */
li:first-child {
  border-top: none;
}

/* Last child */
li:last-child {
  border-bottom: 1px solid gray;
}

/* Every other (zebra striping) */
tr:nth-child(even) {
  background: #f5f5f5;
}

/* Only child */
.sidebar:only-child {
  width: 100%;
}

/* First of type */
article h2:first-of-type {
  font-size: 2rem;
}
```

### Form Pseudo-classes
```css
/* Valid input */
input:valid {
  border-color: green;
}

/* Invalid input */
input:invalid {
  border-color: red;
}

/* Required fields */
input:required {
  background: #fff8e1;
}

/* Placeholder shown */
input:placeholder-shown {
  font-style: italic;
}
```

## Attribute Selectors

```css
/* Has attribute */
[disabled] {
  opacity: 0.5;
}

/* Exact value */
[type="submit"] {
  background: blue;
}

/* Contains value */
[class*="card"] {
  border-radius: 8px;
}

/* Starts with value */
[href^="https"] {
  color: green;
}

/* Ends with value */
[href$=".pdf"] {
  background: url(pdf-icon.svg);
}
```

## Specificity

Specificity determines which styles apply when selectors conflict.

### Specificity Hierarchy

1. **Inline styles** - `style="..."` (1000 points)
2. **IDs** - `#header` (100 points)
3. **Classes, attributes, pseudo-classes** - `.btn`, `[type="text"]`, `:hover` (10 points)
4. **Elements, pseudo-elements** - `p`, `::before` (1 point)

### Examples

```css
/* Specificity: 001 */
p { color: red; }

/* Specificity: 010 */
.text { color: blue; }  /* Wins! */

/* Specificity: 100 */
#intro { color: green; }  /* Wins! */

/* Specificity: 110 */
#intro .text { color: purple; }  /* Wins! */

/* Specificity: 011 */
.text:hover { color: orange; }
```

### Best Practices

1. **Prefer classes over IDs** for styling
   ```css
   /* Good */
   .nav-link { ... }

   /* Avoid */
   #nav-link { ... }  /* Too specific, hard to override */
   ```

2. **Don't over-qualify selectors**
   ```css
   /* Bad - too specific */
   div.container > ul.nav > li.nav-item > a.nav-link { ... }

   /* Good */
   .nav-link { ... }
   ```

3. **Use the cascade, not !important**
   ```css
   /* Avoid */
   .btn { color: red !important; }

   /* Better - increase specificity naturally */
   .btn.primary { color: blue; }
   ```

## Quick Reference

| Selector | Target | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `*` | All elements | `* { margin: 0; }` |
| `element` | By tag | `p { }` |
| `.class` | By class | `.btn { }` |
| `#id` | By ID | `#header { }` |
| `A B` | Descendant | `.card h2 { }` |
| `A > B` | Direct child | `.card > h2 { }` |
| `A + B` | Adjacent sibling | `h2 + p { }` |
| `A ~ B` | General sibling | `h2 ~ p { }` |
| `:hover` | Hover state | `.btn:hover { }` |
| `:focus` | Focus state | `input:focus { }` |
| `:first-child` | First child | `li:first-child { }` |
| `:last-child` | Last child | `li:last-child { }` |
| `:nth-child(n)` | Nth child | `tr:nth-child(odd) { }` |
| `[attr]` | Has attribute | `[disabled] { }` |
| `[attr=value]` | Exact match | `[type="text"] { }` |

**Remember:**
- ✅ Use classes for most styling
- ✅ Keep specificity as low as possible
- ✅ Avoid IDs for styling
- ✅ Use pseudo-classes for interactivity
- ✅ Avoid !important
- ❌ Don't use inline styles (except dynamic JS values)

# Essential to know
- Every element is a box: content + padding + border + margin
- `box-sizing: border-box` includes padding/border in width
- `margin` is space outside, `padding` is space inside
- Use `border-box` globally for predictable sizing

---

# The Box Model

Every HTML element is a rectangular box. Understanding how these boxes work is essential for layout.

## The Four Parts of the Box Model

```
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│         Margin              │
│   ┌─────────────────────┐   │
│   │      Border         │   │
│   │   ┌─────────────┐   │   │
│   │   │   Padding   │   │   │
│   │   │   ┌─────┐   │   │   │
│   │   │   │Content│   │   │   │
│   │   │   └─────┘   │   │   │
│   │   └─────────────┘   │   │
│   └─────────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────┘
```

1. **Content** - The actual content (text, images)
2. **Padding** - Space between content and border
3. **Border** - The edge around padding
4. **Margin** - Space outside the border (separates elements)

## Box Model Properties

### Width and Height
```css
.box {
  width: 300px;
  height: 200px;
  background: lightblue;
}
```

### Padding (Inside Space)
```css
/* All sides */
.box {
  padding: 20px;
}

/* Vertical | Horizontal */
.box {
  padding: 10px 20px;
}

/* Top | Horizontal | Bottom */
.box {
  padding: 10px 20px 15px;
}

/* Top | Right | Bottom | Left */
.box {
  padding: 10px 20px 15px 25px;
}

/* Individual sides */
.box {
  padding-top: 10px;
  padding-right: 20px;
  padding-bottom: 15px;
  padding-left: 25px;
}
```

### Border
```css
.box {
  /* Shorthand: width style color */
  border: 2px solid black;

  /* Or individual properties */
  border-width: 2px;
  border-style: solid;  /* solid, dashed, dotted, double */
  border-color: black;

  /* Individual sides */
  border-top: 3px dashed red;
  border-radius: 8px;  /* Rounded corners */
}
```

### Margin (Outside Space)
```css
.box {
  /* All sides */
  margin: 20px;

  /* Vertical | Horizontal */
  margin: 10px auto;  /* auto centers horizontally */

  /* Individual sides */
  margin-top: 10px;
  margin-right: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  margin-left: 20px;
}
```

## The box-sizing Property

This is crucial for predictable sizing!

### content-box (Default - Problematic)
```css
.box {
  box-sizing: content-box;  /* Default */
  width: 300px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 5px solid black;
  /* Actual width = 300 + 40 + 10 = 350px! */
}
```

### border-box (Recommended)
```css
.box {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  width: 300px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 5px solid black;
  /* Actual width = 300px (padding/border included) */
}
```

### Always Use border-box
```css
/* Reset box-sizing globally */
*,
*::before,
*::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

## Margin Behavior

### Margin Collapse
Vertical margins can collapse (combine) instead of adding:

```css
.box1 { margin-bottom: 20px; }
.box2 { margin-top: 30px; }
/* Actual space between = 30px (not 50px!) */
```

### Margin Auto
Center block elements horizontally:

```css
.container {
  width: 80%;
  margin: 0 auto;  /* Top/bottom: 0, Left/right: auto */
}
```

## Practical Examples

### Card Component
```css
.card {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  width: 300px;
  padding: 24px;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  border-radius: 8px;
  margin: 16px;
  background: white;
}

.card-title {
  margin-top: 0;  /* Remove default margin */
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.card-content {
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.card-button {
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
```

### Navigation Bar
```css
.navbar {
  padding: 1rem 2rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.nav-item {
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  margin-right: 1rem;
}
```

## Debugging the Box Model

Use browser DevTools to visualize:

1. Right-click element → Inspect
2. Look at the "Computed" tab
3. See the box model diagram
4. Colors usually indicate:
   - Blue: Content
   - Green: Padding
   - Orange: Margin

Or add this helper CSS:
```css
/* Debug all boxes */
* {
  outline: 1px solid red;
}

/* Or use specific colors for each */
body * {
  background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1);
  outline: 1px solid red;
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Container with Max-Width
```css
.container {
  width: 90%;
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 20px;
}
```

### Full-Width Sections with Internal Padding
```css
.section {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 4rem 2rem;
}

.section-content {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

### Inline Elements vs Block Elements

**Block elements** (respect all box model properties):
- `div`, `p`, `h1-h6`, `section`, `article`
- Default: width: 100%, stack vertically

**Inline elements** (only horizontal margins/padding):
- `span`, `a`, `strong`, `em`
- Flow with text, ignore width/height

**Inline-block** (best of both):
```css
.badge {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 4px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  margin-right: 8px;
}
```

## Quick Reference

```css
/* Reset box-sizing */
* { box-sizing: border-box; }

/* Common pattern */
.component {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 600px;
  padding: 24px;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  margin: 0 auto 16px;
  border-radius: 8px;
}
```

**Remember:**
- ✅ Always use `box-sizing: border-box`
- ✅ Use padding for space inside, margin for space outside
- ✅ Use `margin: 0 auto` to center block elements
- ✅ Remember margin collapse on vertical margins
- ✅ Check DevTools when debugging sizing issues
- ❌ Don't mix padding and width without border-box
- ❌ Don't forget that inline elements ignore vertical margins

# Essential to know
- Colors: named `red`, hex `#ff0000`, rgb `rgb(255,0,0)`, hsl
- `font-family`, `font-size`, `font-weight`, `line-height`
- `text-align`, `text-decoration`, `text-transform`
- Use `rem` for font sizes (relative to root)

---

# Colors & Typography

Good use of color and typography makes your websites readable, accessible, and professional.

## CSS Colors

### Named Colors
140 predefined color names:
```css
.primary { color: blue; }
.danger { color: red; }
.success { color: green; }
```

### Hexadecimal (Hex)
Six-digit code representing RGB:
```css
/* Full notation */
.red { color: #ff0000; }
.blue { color: #0000ff; }
.gray { color: #808080; }

/* Short notation (when pairs match) */
.red { color: #f00; }      /* Same as #ff0000 */
.white { color: #fff; }    /* Same as #ffffff */

/* With transparency (alpha) */
.semi-transparent {
  color: #ff000080;  /* 50% transparent red */
  /* Or use 8 digits: #RRGGBBAA */
}
```

### RGB / RGBA
Red, Green, Blue (0-255), plus optional Alpha (0-1):
```css
.red { color: rgb(255, 0, 0); }
.blue { color: rgb(0, 0, 255); }

/* With transparency */
.semi-blue { color: rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.5); }
```

### HSL / HSLA
Hue (0-360°), Saturation (%), Lightness (%):
```css
/* Hue: 0=red, 120=green, 240=blue */
.red { color: hsl(0, 100%, 50%); }
.pastel-blue { color: hsl(240, 50%, 75%); }

/* With transparency */
.see-through { color: hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.3); }
```

**Why use HSL?**
- Easier to create color variations
- Adjust lightness for hover states
- More intuitive than RGB

```css
/* Color variations with HSL */
.primary { color: hsl(220, 80%, 50%); }
.primary-light { color: hsl(220, 80%, 70%); }
.primary-dark { color: hsl(220, 80%, 30%); }
```

## Typography Fundamentals

### Font Family
```css
/* System fonts (fastest, no download) */
body {
  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto,
    Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, sans-serif;
}

/* Web fonts (Google Fonts) */
body {
  font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
}

/* Fallback stack */
body {
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

### Font Size
```css
/* Absolute units (generally avoid) */
.pixel { font-size: 16px; }

/* Relative units (recommended) */
html { font-size: 16px; }  /* Root size */

.rem { font-size: 1.5rem; }     /* 24px (1.5 * 16) */
.rem-large { font-size: 2rem; } /* 32px */
```

**Why use rem?**
- Scales with user preferences (accessibility)
- Consistent across the site
- Easy to change globally

### Font Weight
```css
.light { font-weight: 300; }
.normal { font-weight: 400; }
.medium { font-weight: 500; }
.semibold { font-weight: 600; }
.bold { font-weight: 700; }
```

### Line Height
```css
/* Unitless (recommended - scales with font size) */
body {
  line-height: 1.6;  /* 1.6 times the font size */
}

/* Fixed (rarely used) */
.fixed { line-height: 24px; }
```

**Recommended line heights:**
- Body text: 1.5 - 1.7
- Headings: 1.2 - 1.3
- Code: 1.4 - 1.5

## Text Styling

### Text Align
```css
.left { text-align: left; }      /* Default */
.center { text-align: center; }
.right { text-align: right; }
.justify { text-align: justify; } /* Even edges */
```

### Text Decoration
```css
/* Remove underline from links */
a { text-decoration: none; }

/* Add underline */
.underline { text-decoration: underline; }

/* Strikethrough */
.strike { text-decoration: line-through; }

/* Wavy underline */
.wavy {
  text-decoration: underline wavy red;
}
```

### Text Transform
```css
.uppercase { text-transform: uppercase; }
.lowercase { text-transform: lowercase; }
.capitalize { text-transform: capitalize; }  /* First letter */
```

### Letter and Word Spacing
```css
/* Space between letters */
.spaced { letter-spacing: 0.05em; }

/* Space between words */
.wide { word-spacing: 0.2em; }
```

## Complete Typography Example

```css
/* Root settings */
html {
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

body {
  font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
  color: #1a1a1a;
}

/* Headings */
h1 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;  /* 40px */
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 2rem;    /* 32px */
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1.3;
  margin-top: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

h3 {
  font-size: 1.5rem;  /* 24px */
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1.4;
}

/* Body text */
p {
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  max-width: 65ch;  /* Optimal reading width */
}

/* Links */
a {
  color: hsl(220, 80%, 50%);
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

/* Special text */
.lead {
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  color: #4a4a4a;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.muted {
  color: #6b7280;
}

.code {
  font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', monospace;
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  background: #f3f4f6;
  padding: 0.125rem 0.25rem;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
```

## Color Best Practices

### Create a Color Palette
```css
:root {
  /* Primary */
  --primary-50: hsl(220, 100%, 97%);
  --primary-100: hsl(220, 100%, 90%);
  --primary-500: hsl(220, 80%, 50%);
  --primary-600: hsl(220, 80%, 40%);
  --primary-900: hsl(220, 80%, 20%);

  /* Neutrals */
  --gray-50: hsl(0, 0%, 97%);
  --gray-100: hsl(0, 0%, 90%);
  --gray-500: hsl(0, 0%, 50%);
  --gray-900: hsl(0, 0%, 10%);

  /* Semantic */
  --success: hsl(140, 60%, 40%);
  --warning: hsl(40, 90%, 50%);
  --error: hsl(0, 70%, 50%);
}

.button-primary {
  background: var(--primary-500);
  color: white;
}

.button-primary:hover {
  background: var(--primary-600);
}
```

### Ensure Contrast (Accessibility)
Use a contrast checker to ensure text is readable:
- Normal text: minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio
- Large text: minimum 3:1 contrast ratio

## Quick Reference

```css
/* Colors */
color: red;                  /* Named */
color: #ff0000;             /* Hex */
color: rgb(255, 0, 0);      /* RGB */
color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5); /* RGBA */
color: hsl(0, 100%, 50%);   /* HSL */

/* Typography */
font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
font-size: 1rem;            /* 16px at root */
font-weight: 400;           /* Normal */
line-height: 1.6;

/* Text styling */
text-align: center;
text-decoration: underline;
text-transform: uppercase;
letter-spacing: 0.05em;
```

**Remember:**
- ✅ Use rem for font sizes (accessible)
- ✅ Set line-height unitless (1.5-1.7 for body)
- ✅ Use HSL for easier color variations
- ✅ Ensure sufficient color contrast
- ✅ Limit to 2-3 font families per site
- ✅ Use CSS custom properties for colors
- ❌ Don't use px for font sizes (breaks accessibility)
- ❌ Don't use too many different font sizes

# Essential to know
- `px` - fixed pixels
- `rem` - relative to root font size (best for font sizes)
- `em` - relative to parent font size
- `%` - relative to parent
- `vw`/`vh` - viewport width/height

---

# CSS Units

Choosing the right units is crucial for responsive, maintainable, and accessible designs.

## Absolute Units

### Pixels (px)
Fixed-size units that don't scale:

```css
.box {
  width: 300px;
  border: 2px solid black;
  font-size: 16px;
}
```

**When to use px:**
- Border widths
- Box shadows
- Small details (under 5px)
- Image dimensions

**When NOT to use px:**
- Font sizes (breaks user preferences)
- Component padding/margins (not scalable)

## Relative Units

### rem (Root EM)
Relative to the root (`html`) font size (default 16px):

```css
html {
  font-size: 16px;  /* Base size */
}

.heading {
  font-size: 2rem;      /* 32px */
  margin-bottom: 1rem;  /* 16px */
  padding: 1.5rem;      /* 24px */
}
```

**Why rem is best for fonts:**
- Scales with user browser preferences
- Consistent across the entire site
- Easy to change globally by adjusting root size

**Changing root size:**
```css
html {
  font-size: 18px;  /* Now 1rem = 18px */
}
/* All rem values scale proportionally */
```

### em
Relative to the parent's font size:

```css
.parent {
  font-size: 20px;
}

.child {
  font-size: 1.5em;    /* 30px (1.5 * 20) */
  padding: 1em;        /* 20px */
  margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* 10px */
}
```

**When to use em:**
- Component padding/margins (scales with component)
- Icon sizing relative to text
- Button padding

```css
.button {
  font-size: 1rem;
  padding: 0.5em 1em;  /* Scales with button size */
}

.button-large {
  font-size: 1.25rem;  /* Padding automatically scales */
}
```

**Caution with em:**
- Can compound unexpectedly in nested elements
- Harder to track than rem

### Percentage (%)
Relative to the parent element:

```css
.parent {
  width: 800px;
}

.child {
  width: 50%;     /* 400px */
  padding: 10%;   /* 80px (10% of width) */
}
```

**Common uses:**
- Container widths
- Responsive images
- Fluid layouts

```css
.container {
  width: 90%;
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.responsive-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}
```

## Viewport Units

### vw (Viewport Width)
1vw = 1% of viewport width

```css
.full-width {
  width: 100vw;  /* Full viewport width */
}

.half-width {
  width: 50vw;
}

/* Typography */
.hero-title {
  font-size: 5vw;  /* Scales with viewport */
}
```

### vh (Viewport Height)
1vh = 1% of viewport height

```css
.full-height {
  height: 100vh;  /* Full viewport height */
}

.hero-section {
  min-height: 80vh;
}
```

### vmin / vmax
- vmin: smaller of vw or vh
- vmax: larger of vw or vh

```css
.square {
  width: 50vmin;   /* Always square, scales with smaller dimension */
  height: 50vmin;
}
```

## Other Units

### ch (Character Width)
Width of the '0' character (useful for text columns):

```css
.readable {
  max-width: 65ch;  /* Optimal line length for reading */
}
```

### ex (x-height)
Height of lowercase 'x' (rarely used):

```css
.icon {
  height: 2ex;  /* Scales with font */
}
```

## Unit Comparison Table

| Unit | Relative To | Best For |
|------|-------------|----------|
| `px` | Nothing (fixed) | Borders, shadows |
| `rem` | Root font size | Font sizes, spacing |
| `em` | Parent font size | Component padding |
| `%` | Parent element | Widths, fluid layouts |
| `vw` | Viewport width | Full-width elements |
| `vh` | Viewport height | Full-height sections |
| `ch` | Character width | Text column widths |

## Practical Examples

### Responsive Container
```css
.container {
  width: 90%;              /* Fluid width */
  max-width: 1200px;       /* But not too wide */
  margin: 0 auto;          /* Centered */
  padding: 2rem;           /* Consistent spacing */
}
```

### Scalable Typography System
```css
html {
  font-size: 16px;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  html {
    font-size: 18px;
  }
}

h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; }  /* 40px → 45px */
h2 { font-size: 2rem; }    /* 32px → 36px */
h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; }  /* 24px → 27px */
```

### Hero Section
```css
.hero {
  min-height: 100vh;           /* Full viewport height */
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 2rem;
}

.hero-title {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);  /* Responsive scaling */
}
```

### Card Component (em for internal spacing)
```css
.card {
  font-size: 1rem;
}

.card-title {
  font-size: 1.25em;       /* 20px */
  margin-bottom: 0.5em;    /* 10px */
}

.card-content {
  padding: 1.5em;          /* 24px */
}

/* If we change card font-size, everything scales */
.card-large {
  font-size: 1.25rem;      /* Now padding is 30px, title is 25px */
}
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

### ❌ Mixing units inconsistently
```css
/* Bad */
h1 { font-size: 32px; }
h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
h3 { font-size: 1.2em; }

/* Good - use rem for fonts */
h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; }
```

### ❌ Using px for everything
```css
/* Bad - not accessible */
.button {
  font-size: 14px;
  padding: 8px 16px;
}

/* Good */
.button {
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
}
```

### ❌ Not understanding em compounding
```css
.parent { font-size: 20px; }
.child { font-size: 1.5em; }    /* 30px */
.grandchild { font-size: 1.5em; } /* 45px (1.5 * 30)! */
```

## Best Practices Summary

1. **Font sizes:** Use `rem`
2. **Component spacing:** Use `rem` or `em`
3. **Layout widths:** Use `%` with `max-width`
4. **Full viewport:** Use `vw`/`vh`
5. **Borders/shadows:** Use `px`
6. **Text columns:** Use `ch`

## Quick Reference

```css
/* Typography */
font-size: 1rem;        /* 16px at default */
font-size: 1.125rem;    /* 18px */

/* Spacing */
margin: 1rem;
padding: 1.5rem;

/* Layout */
width: 90%;
max-width: 1200px;
min-height: 100vh;

/* Text readability */
max-width: 65ch;
line-height: 1.6;
```

**Remember:**
- ✅ Use rem for font sizes (accessible)
- ✅ Use % for fluid layouts
- ✅ Use vh/vw for viewport-relative sizing
- ✅ Use em for component-internal spacing
- ✅ Use px only for borders and small details
- ❌ Don't use px for font sizes
- ❌ Don't overuse em (compounding issues)
- ❌ Don't forget user preferences matter
